8frm16.showPrevMessage?topicID=381.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm16.showNextMessage?topicID=381.topic"> Next Topic >> </a> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95% cellpadding=5 cellspacing=1><tr><td valign=top bgcolor=#cccccc class=headings><font color=#8b1a1a>Author</font></td><td valign=top bgcolor=#cccccc class=headings><font color=#8b1a1a>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uventar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ventar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/1/02 2:24:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=381.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> one part of FD fixed</span><hr size=1> Just noticed tonight, after last patch, FD no longer pauses if you FD and try to get up real fast.  Usually we would clear the pause by sitting and then standing real fast.  Instead, when you get up from FD, it automatically shows that you get up from a sitting position (like it automatically sit/stands you).  I think thats how they got around to fixing it. <p><BR> <BR> [60 Grandmaster] <a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=243879   target="web"> <b>Ventar</b></a>   (Iksar) LFG
<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bmonklybusiness43508.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=sytharin>Sytharin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk-in-Training</span><br>  Posts: 66<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/1/02 4:49:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=381.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: one part of FD fixed</span><hr size=1> yeah, its nice.  I dont have to keep the new Iksar models on anymore.  The only new model I used was Iksar because they didnt have this problem. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=205007>Sytharin</a>
<BR>
Level 38 Iksar monk<BR>
Dolce Vendetta<BR>
Bristlebane</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ujheransanarcoleptic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jheran Sanarcoleptic</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/1/02 8:17:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=381.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> No, it's not fixed, just covered up</span><hr size=1> I personally don't like it. Here is why...<br>
<br>
If you fd close to a mob, and cycle through sitting then standing, do you get the increased agro range that you do from sitting? Sure, you immediately stand, but if this is the case, then you may run the risk of getting agro from a mob now that you would not have before.<br>
<br>
Secondly, the screen bobbing down then up is annoying. It's also confusing because I initially thought that I was beginning to sit, hit the sit button, and sat down. This caught me off guard the first time or two I did it, and it still makes me do a double take. Being distracted while fd splitting tough mobs is the last thing we need.<br>
<br>
IMO, Verant cheated. Instead of fixing the issue with their code that caused the pause, they added a useless animation to cover it up and possibly made our job a little harder. The pause is still there, it's just hidden by the annoying sit to stand. I had no problem at all with the pause...I was aware of it and had accounted for it when splitting. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=310212"target=_blank><B>Jheran Sanarcoleptic</B></a><BR>
56 Monk <BR>
Lords of Shadowed Blade <BR>
Lover of Bananas
 <br><a href="http://spacefem.com/uselessquiz/index.shtml">
 <img src="http://spacefem.com/uselessquiz/9.gif" border=0>
 </a><br>
 </p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ujheransanarcoleptic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jheran Sanarcoleptic</A> at: 10/1/02 8:19:02 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukuririnpureheart7th.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KuririnPureheart7th</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/1/02 10:36:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=381.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: No, it's not fixed, just covered up</span><hr size=1> Uh.. it adds no aggro, thats why if you have aggro on a mob and sit, it turns to you, but as soon as it stands it turns away (provided it's actually aggroed on someone else)... and its hardly confusing, i sit pull a lot to keep aggro off casters, if it bugs you that much... well i dont know, dont use fd or something *shrug* <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukorph.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Korph</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Disciple</span><br>  Posts: 254<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/1/02 12:51:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=381.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: No, it's not fixed, just covered up</span><hr size=1> Agro radius is larger while sitting. <p>-Korph
<br>
<br>
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=308735"><img src="http://gjband.com/Sig.jpg"><br>Level 51 Disciple</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bmonklybusiness43508.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=buffman>buffman</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 200<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/2/02 2:01:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=381.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: No, it's not fixed, just covered up</span><hr size=1> the only problem with that is... at no point are you sitting. you're in the process of standing that's all. <p><center><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=28663">Magelo Profile</A></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umezu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mezu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/2/02 2:13:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=381.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: No, it's not fixed, just covered up</span><hr size=1> I like the change, effectively removes the period where you cannot move when you FD and immediately get up again (well, for Iksars, Human monks never had the problem afaik).<br>
<br>
You're never really sitting.. I don't think it even shows you as 'getting up' to other people.<br>
<br>
Swilver,<br>
Grandmaster of Bristlebane <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ujheransanarcoleptic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jheran Sanarcoleptic</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 33<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/2/02 9:12:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=381.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: No, it's not fixed, just covered up</span><hr size=1> Human monks did have this problem. If you checked my profile, you will see that I am human.<br>
<br>
You say that at no point are you sitting...I do believe you go from prone, to sit to stand. In alternate views it cycles through sitting to standing, and others see me as popping up to sit then immediately standing. <br>
<br>
The only way to truly know if you are sitting as far as the game and surrounding mobs are concerned would be to look at the code. However, from the animation I'm suspicious that you do sit before standing, albeit for a very short amount of time.<br>
<br>
