<br>
No, its not there...  As an Iksar, while running from place to place, I often practice FD...  My FD is hot key'd to 6 and my sit/stand was hot key'd to 7...  Before the patch, I would hit 6 and have to mash 7 three times (stand-sit-stand) or else I'd be 'stunned' for about 2 seconds...  Same for the case when I would 'fall to the ground', I would have to mash 7 three times to run away or else have to endure a round of attacks...  Post patch, I can hit 6 then 7 and not even break stride when running from place to place...<br>
<br>
 &quot;I had no problem at all with the pause...&quot;<br>
<br>
That's because you are human, the pause was a PITA for us Iksars... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ujheransanarcoleptic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jheran Sanarcoleptic</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 35<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/7/02 11:01:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=381.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: No, it's not fixed, just covered up</span><hr size=1> The pause was there for us, but it sounds like it was a lot shorter...less than a second, but enough to screw us up too if you expected to be able to move right away. Glad they fixed it for you scaly types. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=310212"target=_blank><B>Jheran Sanarcoleptic</B></a><BR>
